text:
="preserve">Mohammad Khaledur Rahman Tito (1946 – 10 January 2021) was a Bangladesh Awami League politician. He was a member of the Awami League. In 1986, he was elected to the Jatiya Sangsad. He left the job in 1988 and was re-elect to the parliament in 2008. Tito retired in 2014.
Tito died on 10 January 2021 in Jessore, Bangladesh at the age of 74.
